20/07/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- An ad hoc committee of parliament approved on Friday (18 July) the draft constitutional changes designed to bring legislation into line with EU standards.
Members of the committee unanimously supported the amendments concerning the immunity and mandate of magistrates.
The committee decided the draft amendments would be submitted to parliament for debate by the end of the month.
The amendments require three rounds of voting.
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 19/07/03;
BTA, AFP - 18/07/03)
